LAGOS, February 13 The following are major news items in leading Nigerian
newspapers Sunday. The Guardian: -- The Nigerian House of Representatives
is currently working on legislative procedure to enact a law to deal with
the problem of desertification in the most populous African country,
according to Speaker Alhaji Ghali Umar Na'aba. New Nigerian: -- The
Nigerian government has been advised to resist any pressure to implement
policies like the deregulation of prices of petroleum products which will
impact negatively the economic well-being of Nigerians. The Post Express:
-- Governor of Lagos State, Senator Bola Tinubu, has recently announced
plans to begin the modernization of the water front of Lagos, Nigeria's
biggest city, in an effort to create more jobs and boost tourism of the
state.
